  "texts": [
    "If f sits on the outer boundary then the region C f decomposes into two non-empty regions C in and C out, where C in consists of the vertices and edges of C f that are entirely contained in Σ C, and C out consists of the vertices and edges that are entirely contained in Σ c C. Let N in:= ∂Σ C in ∩ ∂Σ C be the decorated submanifold shared by ∂Σ C in and ∂Σ C. Let us specialise to the case where C in 0 consists of the left two vertices of the face f and the edge between them.",
    "By writing B f as Let D = C ⊔ I C ′ be a finite connected region obtained by gluing C and C ′ along a self-avoiding dual path I as described in Section 4.9.",
    "Then all inner boundary components of Σ C are also inner boundary components of Σ D. Let C be an anchor of Σ C whose attachment point to the outer boundary component S C 0 of Σ C also lies on the outer boundary component of Σ D. Let D be an anchor for Σ D such that S D 0 is the outer boundary of Σ D and such that S C κ = S D κ+λ for κ = 1, • • •, m and some fixed offset λ ∈ {0, 1, • • •, n -m}.",
    "If the graph of D moreover contains the graph of C as a subgraph, then we say D extends C with offset λ.",
    "More generally, any anchor ′ D ∼ D is also said to extend C with offset λ."
  ],
